msgid "Client-side Data Storage FAQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:5
msgid "Mobile Web Experience"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:7
msgid "**1. What data is stored?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:8
msgid ""
"Similar to a desktop web browser, data may be stored in the mobile web "
"browser cache which resides on the storage system of the device operating"
" system which is protected by security measures in the physical device "
"and its operating system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:9
msgid "**2. How is the data protected?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:10
msgid ""
"Security for mobile web experience is similar to the security for a "
"desktop web experience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:13
msgid "**3. When is the data deleted?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:12
msgid ""
"If you log out or your account is deactivated, the data in the browser "
"cache may reside until the cache expires or the temporary file system "
"store on the operating system is cleared, depending on your operating "
"system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:16
msgid "Mobile App Experience"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:18
msgid ""
"To speed up initial loading time, Mattermost mobile apps cache data "
"locally on the device for v1.1 and later. Below are common questions on "
"cached data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:20
msgid ""
"**1. What data is stored locally with the new mobile apps on a mobile "
"device?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:22
msgid ""
"The data that can be found on the device depends solely on whether or not"
" the user is logged in to the Mattermost server, and is independent of "
"the state of the device's connection or the state of the app. While "
"logged in, anything that the user is normally allowed to see is eligible "
"for storage on the device, which includes the following content:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:24
msgid "messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:25
msgid "files and images that are attached to messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:26
msgid ""
"avatars, usernames, and email addresses of people in the currently open "
"channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:28
msgid ""
"In addition, metadata that the app uses for keeping track of its "
"operations is also cached. The metadata includes user IDs, channel IDs, "
"team IDs, and message IDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:30
msgid "Currently, cache cannot be reset remotely on connected mobile devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:33
msgid "**2. What about push notifications?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:33
msgid ""
"Push notification storage is managed by the operating system on the "
"device. Mattermost can be configured to send limited amounts of "
"information that does not include the message text or channel name, and "
"it can also be configured to not send push notifications at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:36
msgid "**3. Where is the data stored and how is that data protected?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:36
msgid ""
"The data is stored in the app's local storage. It is protected by the "
"security measures that a device normally provides to the apps that are "
"installed on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:39
msgid "**4. How long is the data stored?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:39
msgid ""
"Data is stored until the user logs out, or until it is purged during "
"normal cache management. Deactivating a user account forces a logout and "
"subsequent purging of data from the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:42
msgid "**5. Are messages pre-loaded?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:42
msgid ""
"No. Messages are sent to the device on demand. They are not pre-loaded in"
" anticipation of users scrolling up or switching channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:45
msgid ""
"**6. What happens to messages that are deleted on the server after a user"
" has seen them?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:45
msgid "The messages are deleted from the client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:55
msgid ""
"**7. What data is stored on a mobile device after an account is "
"deactivated in the following cases:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:48
msgid "*The mobile device is connected with app running.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:49
msgid ""
"All the data listed in Questions 1 and 2, but within 60 seconds after an "
"account is deactivated on the server, all app data is deleted from the "
"cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:50
msgid "*The mobile device is disconnected with app running.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:51
msgid ""
"All the data listed in Questions 1 and 2, but within 60 seconds after the"
" device reconnects, all app data is deleted from the cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:52
msgid "*The mobile device is connected with the app not running.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:53
msgid ""
"All the data listed in Questions 1 and 2, but within 60 seconds after the"
" app is started, all app data is deleted from the cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:54
msgid "*The mobile device is disconnected and app is not running.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:55
msgid ""
"All the data listed in Questions 1 and 2, but within 60 seconds after the"
" device reconnects and the app is started, all app data is deleted from "
"the cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:57
msgid ""
"**8. What data might be on the device after a user account is deactivated"
" and all data is deleted from the cache?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/client-side-data.rst:58
msgid ""
"If file attachments are enabled on the server, users can download files "
"that are attached to messages and store them on their local file system. "
"After they are downloaded, the files are outside the control of the app "
"and can remain on the device indefinitely."
msgstr ""

